52 If Jupiter wearied his smith from whom 53 he took, being angered, the sharp lightning 54 with which on the last day I was struck;
55 or if he wearied the others, in turns, 56 in Mongibello at the dark forge, 57 calling “Good Vulcan, help, help!”,
