query.result:
106 His head is formed of fine gold,
107 and pure silver are the arms and the chest,
108 then he is of copper up to the fork;

109 from there downwards he is all elect iron,
110 save that the right foot is baked earth;
111 and he stands on that, more than on the other, erect.

115 Their course crashes into this valley;
116 they make Acheron, Styx and Phlegethon;
117 then they go down through this narrow stream,

118 until, there where one no longer dismounts,
119 they make Cocytus; and what that pool is
120 you will see, therefore it is not counted here.

124 And he to me: “You know that the place is round;
125 and all that you have come very much,
126 always to the left, descending down to the bottom,

127 you have not yet turned through all the circle;
128 therefore, if a new thing appears to you,
129 do not show wonder on your face.”
